Notification of Government Security Activity and Visitor Group Security Agreements
column5:
In solicitations and contracts which require a DD Form 254 for performance on U.S. Government installations and overseas.

Notify OESRC
column6:
Negotiation Position #1:  Contract Does Not Include a DD Form 254:

This clause is prescribed at AFFARS 5304.404-90 to be used in solicitations and contracts that require a DD Form 254, DOD Contract Security Classification Specification, and requires performance at a government location in the U.S. or overseas.  This contract does not include a DD Form 254.  Therefore, it is requested for this clause to be removed for clarity. Thank you. 

Negotiation Position #2:  Contract will not be Performed on a government location in the U.S. or overseas.  

This clause is prescribed at AFFARS 5304.404-90 to be used in solicitations and contracts that require a DD Form 254, DOD Contract Security Classification Specification, and requires performance at a government location in the U.S. or overseas.  The contract will not be performed at a government location in the U.S. or overseas. Therefore, it is requested for this clause to be removed for clarity. Thank you

column2: Organizational Conflict of Interest
column5: There are six (6) versions of this clause. The basic clause is to be used when it is determined that Virginia Tech will be providing System Engineering and Technical Direction (SETA) services.  This will impact the university's ability to participate in future efforts. Virginia Tech should not be performing SETA work.  Therefore, please request for the clause's removal.  Thanks.
column6:
Negotiation Position:  Not Executing SETA 

Virginia Tech will be executing research efforts and will not be providing Systems Engineering and Technical Assistance.  Therefore, it is requested for this clause to be removed for clarity. Thank you.

column2: AAFARS 5352.215-9000, Facility Clearance, has been retired.  Request for removal.
column6:
Negotiation Position:  No Longer an Active Clause.  

This clause has been removed from the AAFARS.  Therefore, it is respectfully requested for it to be removed for clarity.  Thank you.

column6: Will not be applicable to Virginia Tech.

column2: Elimination of Use of Class I Ozone Depleting  Substances (ODS)
column5: Documents that Class I Ozone Depleting Substances are not allowed to be used.  If approval has been provided IAW AFI 32-7086, Hazardous Materials Management, Chapter 4,the contract would include FAR 52.223-11.

column2: Health and Safety on Government Installations
column5: Used in solicitations and contracts, other than for construction, which require performance on a Government installation.
column6:
Negotiation Position:  Not Performing on a Government Installation.

Virginia Tech is executing research efforts that will not be performed on a government installation. Since this clause is prescribed at AFFARS 5352.9001 to be included in contracts where performance is on a government installation, it is understood that this clause does not apply.  It is respectfully requested for it to be removed for clarity.  Thank you.

column6:
Negotiation Position:  No Longer an Active Provision.

This provision has been removed from the AAFARS.  Therefore, it is respectfully requested for it to be removed for clarity.  Thank you.

column2: Insurance Certificate Requirements in Spain (USAFE)
column5: In all solicitations and contracts for services to be performed in Spain by other than U.S. or Spanish contractors (i.e., a Third Country National (TCN) contractor).
column6:
Negotiation Position #1:  Indemnification.

As a state agency of the Commonwealth of Virginia, the university is unable to accept the indemnity terms that are included in this clause.  Therefore, it is respectfully requested for this clause to be removed.  Thank you.  

Negotiation Position #2:  Not using a Third Country National to perform services in Spain. 

Virginia Tech is executing research efforts and is not contracting for TCN services in Spain.  For clarity, it is respectfully requested for this clause to be removed.  Thank you.

column2: Contractor Access to Air Force Installations
column5:
If contract requires frequent visits to or performance of work on Air Force installations.

Notify OESRC
column6:
Negotiation Position #1:  Not Performing Work at an Air Force Installation or Making Frequent Visits

This clause is prescribed at AFFARS 5342.490-1 to be used in solicitations and contracts that require contractor personnel to make frequent visits to or perform work on Air Force installation(s).  Since Virginia Tech will be performing research efforts at its own locations, it is understood that this clause does not apply.  It is requested to be removed for clarity.  Thank you.

column2: Common Access Cards (CACs) for Contractor Personnel
column5:
Used in solicitations and contracts that require contractor personnel to meet one or both of the following criteria:

    (a) Require logical access to Department of Defense computer networks and systems in either the unclassified environment or the classified environment where authorized by governing security directives; and/or

    (b) Perform work which requires the use of a CAC for installation entry control or physical access to facilities and buildings.

Notify OESRC
column6:
Negotiation Position #1:  Do Not  Require logical access to Department of Defense computer networks and systems in either the unclassified environment or the classified environment where authorized by governing security directive.  

In the performance of this effort, Virginia Tech does not require logical access to Department of Defense computer networks and systems in either the unclassified environment or the classified environment where authorized by governing security directives. It also will not be performing  work which requires the use of a CAC for installation entry control or physical access to facilities and buildings.Therefore, it is respectfully requested for this clause to be removed.  Thank you. 

Negotiation Position #2:  Not Perfoming work which requires the use of a CAC for installation entry control or physical access to facilities and buildings:

In the performance of this effort, Virginia Tech is not perfoming work which requires the use of a CAC for installation entry control or physical access to facilities and buildings.  Therefore, it is respectfully requested for this clause to be removed.  Thank you.
